No. Only - playing about. My voice sound like my sister then. Like Ellen. And she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 You didn't really take an interest in politics you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 You said you didn't think you were allowed to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 
Well I don't know. The people of them days, the parents didn't let you interfere with anything like that them days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 You didn't vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 
No. Not until - 'til the voting for women come. See I didn't go this year - 'cos I couldn't walk across the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 
Was your spare time different in any way, did you make any new friends at this time? It was rather different because you were living in in service weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 But in your time off then what did you do in your spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 
Well I'd - come home and I'd - have a look around and I'd see what one done, I'd go to one aunt and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Would you make any new friends, boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Only my one boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 How did you meet them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 
Well playing about - like I did before I left school, and that was my husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Did you ever take friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Only him. Oh mind I had girlfriends to come home. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Did you have any special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Yes, I had two or three friends. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 You had the one boy who became your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 And you had a few special girl friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Yes. And she used to say, oh I wouldn't have him.
 I'm not going to kiss a boy - a - they - you know, they used to play about them days, if you - if you let the boy kiss you - you'll have a shilling. And - we daresn't tell my mother. And - I said, oh, there's nothing in it. And my friend got - we all got
 
in this double door, down in our street, and - we had to got the corner because there was a big drapers shop and there was a big entrance in, and - my husband come down, and he used to send a watchdog, to see that we really kissed. And of course he kissed
 me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 
About twelve or thirteen. And he really kissed me, and - they said, there you are, she'll be your wife. And little did we think, and my friend said, I wouldn't kiss him. I'm not going to marry a corner boy, she sai
d. I said, he's not a corner boy. She said, but look at the turn he got in his eye. Well I said he can't help what God afflicted him with. I said, although I don't like a turned eye, not looking at myself mind, anyhow God love him - I had him, and I'd - h
ave him again. For another fifty-two years if it was pleasing to God.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Where would you go with your special friends then in spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 
Well we'd go to cinema or - anywhere like that. Perhaps we'd skip into town, have a little run round town. But if my mother knew we'd get killed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 
Oh she wouldn't let you go in the town. After I left school though, we was allowed to go in, and we used to tell the boys that we were going in to this play house, well that's what it was called, the Play 
House see, blood and thunder we used to call it. And - we'd tell 'em, and they'd go through the streets and they'd go, phew, phew - phew, and we'd know then, and we'd go in - well it was only tuppence to go in. And we'd walk every step of the way in, thro
ugh {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bridge Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, and then coming home - they'd say, do you want a pie Gwen, to my friend. Yes, I'll have a - a nice plum tart - pie. And you got a - oh a beauty - for a penny, and the plums'd be red hot it it, burn your mouth half your time. And then they
'd say do you want fish and chips. Well you could go further down, and you'd have - you'd have the - we used to laugh over it, the fruit first and the fish and chips after. And you'd have a lovely hapenny fish and ha'porth of chips. And plenty of salt and
 vinegar on 'em. People called Mens, in - in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bridge Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} that was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Did they expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Oh they'd want to know where we'd been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Is this when you were in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 
Yes. In service and - and out of service. When I was home - I had to be in just the same. My mother was strict, and - when I was going with my husband when he was only twelve or thirteen coming up
, there was only twelve months between us, and - he'd slip through one street and me the other, well then when he joined up I said to him, I'm not going to write to you because you've got no right to leave your mother. And he said, well our Billy - our Bi
l
ly's gone. I said, I don't care what your Billy's done. 'Course he had to go. And - anyway he wrote - and he said - I've had a letter from Tom and Bill, and you goes to my mother and you won't - write to me. And he said - I know you've got a birthday comi
n
g up, and - I'll send you on a - a - nice little handkerchief. He sent the silk handkerchief with his - badge in the middle. ASC on it see, Army Service Corps. And he was out in Egypt. And he said I've also got a bit - out of the stable of Bethlehem for y
o
u, he wasn't a Catholic then. And - when he come home on leave - he - only whistled by the door and I went out and my mother said - what are you keeping that boy out by the door for lady? And I said - well I don't know mamma, he whistled to me and I went 
o
ut. Well she said if you want to fetch him in bring him in. And from then on - he went back. He wasn't in Egypt then, I'm telling a lie, he was in France. The first world war. That was France then. Well then - he went out to Egypt - he was out to Egypt th
en for four years and ten months. And I was married in 1919 - he come home on June the sixth 1919, and I was married the twenty-sixth of December 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 How old were you then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Twenty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Then you'd known your husband since you were twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 You were in school together you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Not in the same school, he went to Morland school and I went to St Abans.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 How did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Well because they lived around by us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Where did your husband come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 From Splott.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Did you save up money before getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Did your parents help you to set up home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 
My mother set - helped me to get my wedding breakfast but no more. Well she couldn't because she was a widow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 
From the time, the twenty - from sixth of June 'til the twenty-sixth, and my wed - my engagement ring was like that. And it wore thin, and it snapped, and now when I was married forty years that's what he bought me in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place
}}Aldershot{\*\xmlclose}. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15954610 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 Can you remember your wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9640500 MC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14885319\charrsid3419878 
Yes I can. I went over to church a fortnight ago, and - the priest have got to call me Mary because all the others call me Mary do you see, so he said, Mary, he said, it's awfully rude to pass remark, but he said you've
 got the colour of the month non I said, have I father, I don't know what colour it is. He said, purple. Well I said, if you want to know father I said I was married in that colour. Oh he said, Mary, he said, it makes you look years younger. So I said, th
a
nk, you for the compliment, now there was headmistress there by him selling the papers, and she said, take that for a compliment Mrs Cosh. So I said, I got to. I said I was married in this church in purple. So he said, well it do make you look younger Mar
y
. So I said thank you Father, and - I said, and I can remember it as though it was yesterday. I said, fifty-two years, yes, he said, and that's why you grieve so much. Now, he said, you haven't got to grieve. Well I told him then how - I'd - give anything
 a fortnight ago if I could have caught my -
\par }}